seeds.problem_text:
Consider the following region structure on a $5 \times 5$ grid:
\[
\begin{bmatrix}
A & B & C & C & C \\
A & A & D & C & A \\
A & D & D & D & E \\
E & B & D & E & E \\
B & B & B & C & E
\end{bmatrix}
\]
Cells with the same letter belong to the same region.
\begin{definition}[Valid complete grid]
A \emph{valid complete grid} is a completely filled $5 \times 5$ grid with the above region structure such that
\begin{itemize}
\item each row contains the digits $1,2,3,4,5$ exactly once;
\item each column contains the digits $1,2,3,4,5$ exactly once;
\item each region contains the digits $1,2,3,4,5$ exactly once.
\end{itemize}
\end{definition}
\begin{definition}[Minimal puzzle]
A \emph{minimal puzzle} is a partially filled grid (with the same region structure) such that
\begin{itemize}
\item the given clues uniquely determine a valid complete grid;
\item removing any single clue results in multiple possible valid complete grids.
\end{itemize}
\end{definition}
Determine the total number of distinct minimal puzzles for this grid.

