{

The puzzle requires filling a $4\times4\times4$ Latin cube so that:
\begin{enumerate}
\item Each layer is a Latin square on $\{1,2,3,4\}$.
\item Each vertical pillar $(i,j)$ across all four layers contains the digits
$\{1,2,3,4\}$ exactly once.
\item All given numbers match the original puzzle.
\item Each vertical $2\times2$ sub-block (a $2\times2$ region fixed in $(i,j)$
and spanning all layers) must also contain each digit exactly twice
(once in each of two layers), preserving the Latin-cube structure.
\end{enumerate}
The completed layers are:
\[
L_1=\begin{bmatrix}
